title: Rumor: Has Oregon Ducks 4-star QB Seth Green de-committed?
text:
Rivals four-star quarterback Seth Green has not had the senior year he anticipated.
After transferring from Minnesota to Texas powerhouse Allen High School, the 6-foot-4, 210-pound signal-caller has been entrenched in a battle for the starting quarterback role with junior Mitchell Jonke.
At the same time, the Oregon Ducks are unranked for the first time in years and appear desperate to find an answer at the quarterback position, adding a second commitment when ESPN four-star quarterback Terry Wilson flipped from Nebraska .
The Wilson/Green combination is almost certain to produce a (potentially avoidable) quarterback battle in the years to come at Oregon, as the two class of 2016 recruits are similarly ranked. Green is rated as the No. 10 dual-threat quarterback in the country by Rivals, while Wilson is ranked No. 12 at his position and No. 214 overall by ESPN .
Given Green's on-field struggles and the Ducks' recruitment of a second signal-caller, a mutual parting of ways doesn't seem far-fetched, which is why the rumor that Green had de-committed spread like wildfire this weekend on message boards and social media.
It didn't help matters that Green removed all the information from his Twitter bio, including the message that he was committed to Oregon.
Despite the rumors and the profile change, however, Green said over the weekend that his relationship with the Ducks was "still good" and that he "(hasn't) de-committed."
Still, that possibility remains in play.
Fellow commits have indicated that Green's certainty about a future in Eugene has wavered in recent weeks and that they aren't sure where he'll end up.
Where there's this much smoke, there's typically fire.
Consider Green a wait-and-see commit until signing day from here on out.
